Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
01/03/2024
Last Updated:
12/04/2024
This Privacy Policy describes how Pick A Pump ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and shares information about you through our digital properties including our website, mobile application, and services (collectively, the "Platform"). By using our Platform, you agree to the collection, use, and sharing of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.
1. Information Collection
When you use our Platform, we collect the following information:
Account Information:
When you sign up for an account, you provide us with your username, email address, and password. Your password is encrypted before it is stored in our database.
Location Information:
If you permit the app to access your location, we use your location to provide directions and services via the Mapbox API. We do not store your location data or associate it with your personal account information.
Feedback and Reports:
If you submit feedback or report an issue, we collect your username and email address. This information is used solely to follow up with you regarding your report.
Analytics Information:
If you consent to cookies, we use Google GA4 Analytics to collect information about your use of our Platform. This helps us understand how you interact with our services and improve them.
2. Use of Information
We use the information we collect to:
Provide, maintain, and improve our services.
Respond to your feedback or issues.
Enhance the security and safety of our Platform.
Communicate with you about products, services, offers, promotions, and events offered by [Your Company/App Name] and others, and provide news and information we think will be of interest to you.
3. Sharing of Information
We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties for their marketing purposes. We only share your information as follows:
With service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as hosting and maintenance, analysis, customer service, and marketing.
As required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process.
4. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to help protect information about you from loss, theft, misuse and unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
5. Third-Party Services
Our Platform may integrate with third-party services such as but not limited to Mapbox and Google (reCAPTCHA, GA4 Analytics). The use of your information by these third-party services is governed by their privacy policies, not this one.
6. Your Choices
You may update, correct, or delete your account information at any time by logging into your account and managing your profile settings.
8. Data Protection Rights
Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have certain rights regarding your personal data. These include:
Access:
You can request a copy of your personal data.
Rectification:
You can ask us to correct any incorrect or incomplete data.
Erasure:
You may ask us to delete your personal data, subject to certain exceptions.
Restriction:
You can request the restriction of processing of your personal data.
Portability:
You can request the transfer of your personal data to another organisation.
Objection:
You can object to the processing of your personal data.
Automated Decisions:
You have the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing.
9. Lawful Basis for Processing
We process your data based on the following lawful bases:
Consent:
We may process your data when you have given us explicit consent to use your personal data for a specific purpose.
Contract:
Processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party.
Legal Obligation:
Processing is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which we are subject.
z
10. Data Retention
We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes we collected it for, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
11. Data Transfers
Your information, including personal data, may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ from those from your jurisdiction.
12. Cookies and Local Storage
We use cookies and local storage technology to enhance your user experience. Cookies are small text files placed on your device to collect standard internet log information and visitor behavior information. This information is used to track visitor use of the website and to compile statistical reports on website activity.
Pick A Pump uses cookies to collect information about how you use our Platform. This helps us understand user interactions and improve our services. Additionally, third-party services that we integrate with, such as Google GA4 Analytics and Mapbox, may also use cookies.
Google GA4 Analytics:
When you consent to cookies, Google GA4 Analytics collects information such as your IP address, device type, browser type, operating system, pages visited, time spent on pages, and actions taken on our Platform (e.g., clicks, form submissions). This data helps us analyze user behavior and improve our services.
We also use local storage to maintain user session states, such as keeping you logged in. This data is stored securely in your browser and is not shared with third parties.
If you decline cookies, your information will not be saved for that session, and certain functionalities of our Platform may be limited or unavailable.
13. Contact Information
For more information or if you have any concerns, please contact our Data Protection Officer at
joel@pickapump.com
.
14. Changes to This Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
Cookie Policy
Pick A Pump uses some cookies to ensure you get the best experience. You can update this in settings later.
